cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper focuses on the reusability of pre-trained deep convolutional models for image co-localization, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method for evaluating the correlations of descriptors, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
